---
title: Egyptian Inspired Lentils (v) with Dukkah and Goat's Cheese Toast
description: Here’s a 20-minute bowl full of goodness that will nourish you from the inside out. Packed with veg, protein-packed pulses, and delicately seasoned with cinnamon, ginger, turmeric, cumin and chilli- the flavours in this dish are second to none. Serve with grilled goat’s cheese ciabatta and top with nutty dukkah for the final touch. Cosy nights in never looked so delicious.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/egyptian-inspired-lentils-0ee235a3-5c822587.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipecards/card/egyptian-inspired-lentils-5ba4ba3230006c28015e7c22-78372b79.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.co.uk/recipes/egyptian-inspired-lentils-5ba4ba3230006c28015e7c22
author: HelloFresh
time required: 20 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 596 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 11 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 15 g
  protein: 30 g
  sodium: 2 g
  serving size: 795
servings: 2
course: main course
cuisine: Egyptian
---

Halve, peel and chop the @red onion{1}(peeled and chopped into small pieces). Trim the @carrot{1}(trimmed and sliced into thin half moons) (no need to peel). Drain and rinse the @lentils{1}(drained and rinsed) and @chickpeas{1}(drained and rinsed) together in a #colander{}. Set aside.

Heat a splash of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} or #saucepan{} over medium-high heat. Add the onion and carrot. Fry until softened and starting to colour, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Pop the @ginger puree{1}, @cinnamon stick{1}, @ground turmeric{2}, @ground cumin{2}, @chilli flakes{1}(add more if you like some heat!) and @tomato puree{30} into the pan. Stir well. Cook for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the lentils and the chickpeas.

Add the @water{500} (see ingredients for amount) to the pan. Bring to the boil. Add the @vegetable stock powder{1/2} and stir to dissolve. Pop in the @chopped kale{100} and cover the pan with a #lid{} or #foil{}. Cook until the kale is soft, another ~{4-5%minutes}.

Slice the @ciabatta{1} in half lengthways - as if you were making a sandwich! Cut the @goat's cheese{125} log to give you 4 slices per person. Lay the goat's cheese slices over the cut side of the ciabatta. Pop on a lined #baking tray{} and grill on the top shelf of the #oven{}, until the cheese has softened and is starting to colour, ~{3-5%minutes}.

When the kale is ready, remove the cinnamon stick from the lentils. Season to taste with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Serve the lentils in #bowls{} with the goats cheese toast on the side. Sprinkle the @dukkah mix{1} over the toast and lentils. ENJOY!

